  "prompt": "Things: What do you think happens only in India?",
  "response": "Here are some things that are often considered unique to or predominantly found in India:\n\n1. Cultural aspects:\n- Arranged marriages\n- Joint family system\n- Diversity of languages (22 official languages)\n- Caste system\n- Holi festival of colors\n- Diwali celebrations\n\n2. Social practices:\n- Drinking chai (tea) everywhere\n- Negotiating prices in markets\n- Using head nods for communication\n- Eating with hands\n- Removing shoes before entering homes\n\n3. Infrastructure and daily life:\n- Auto rickshaws/tuk-tuks\n- Crowded train travel\n- Cow roaming freely in streets\n- Street food culture\n- Jugaad (innovative problem-solving)\n\n4. Unique phenomena:\n- Cricket being almost a religion\n- Bollywood movie culture\n- Massive public gatherings/festivals\n- Strong emphasis on vegetarianism\n- Colorful traditional clothing like saris\n\n5. Workplace/professional:\n- Very hierarchical work environments\n- Large workforce in IT outsourcing\n- Extended family involvement in career decisions\n\nThese are generalizations and experiences can vary across India's diverse regions and communities.",
